sentence: The war cry for justice was all over - Much to the chagrin of the authorities.
Romanian: Plângerea de război pentru justiție a fost peste tot - mult la chagina autorităților.
backtrans: The war complaint for justice was everywhere - a lot of the authorities' chagin.

sentence: The regime's decision adumbrates the underlying agenda.
Romanian: Decizia regimului emite agenda de bază.
backtrans: The decision of the regime issues the basic agenda.

sentence: The community was anxious over the passing of the much needed reforms.
Romanian: Comunitatea era nerăbdătoare de trecerea reformelor necesare.
backtrans: The community was impatient with the passage of necessary reforms.

sentence: The think tank  published a paper outlining their apology of capital punishment.
Romanian: Think-tank a publicat o lucrare care-și evidențiază scuzele pedepsei capitale.
backtrans: Think-Tank published a work that highlights the excuses of the capital punishment.

sentence: Aught was left of the petition's validity
Romanian: Aught a rămas din valabilitatea petiției
backtrans: Aight remained from the validity of the petition

sentence: The President exhorted his ministers to buckle up as key opposition support for his economic plan was about to buckle.
Romanian: Președintele și-a îndemnat miniștrii să se îndoaie ca sprijinul cheie al opoziției pentru planul său economic a fost pe cataramă.
backtrans: The President urged his ministers to bend as the key support of the opposition for his economic plan was on the buckle.

sentence: The voters were chuffed to see the bill passed.
Romanian: Alegătorii au fost respinși pentru a vedea proiectul de lege.
backtrans: Voters were rejected to see the bill.

sentence: The lawyer's discursive narration swayed the jury.
Romanian: Narațiunea discursivă a avocatului a influențat juriul.
backtrans: The discursive narrative of the lawyer influenced the jury.

sentence: The EU block opposed an eventual imposition of anti-dumping measures.
Romanian: Blocul UE sa opus unei eventuale impuneri de măsuri antidumping.
backtrans: The EU block opposed a possible taxation of anti-dumping measures.

sentence: A fulsome eulogy was delivered by the sly counsel.
Romanian: O eulogie plină a fost trimisă de sfatul Sly.
backtrans: A full eulogy was sent by Sly advice.

sentence: The gig-economy agency decided to garnish the refunds!
Romanian: Agenția Gig-Economia a decis să obțină restituirile!
backtrans: Gig-Economy Agency decided to get refunds!

sentence: Members of the anti-theocratic revolutionary movement overthrew the peers in power!
Romanian: Membrii mișcării revoluționare antisocratice au răsturnat colegii la putere!
backtrans: Members of the antisocratic revolutionary movement have overturned colleagues in power!

sentence: The traitors disappointingly decided to fight with the colonialists.
Romanian: Taranții au decis dezamăgit să lupte cu colonialiștii.
backtrans: The peasants decided disappointed to fight colonialists.
